# Sūra LXXI.: Nūḥ, or Noah.

### Section 1

![](../gif/071/071_001.gif)

1. Inn<u>a</u> arsaln<u>a</u> noo<u>h</u>an il<u>a</u> qawmihi an
an<u>th</u>ir qawmaka min qabli an ya/tiyahum AAa<u>tha</u>bun
aleem**un**

1\. We sent Noah  
To his People  
(With the Command):  
"Do thou warn thy People  
Before there comes to them  
A grievous Penalty."

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/071/071_002.gif)

2. Q<u>a</u>la y<u>a</u> qawmi innee lakum na<u>th</u>eerun mubeen**un**

2\. He said: "O my People!  
I am to you  
A Warner, clear and open:

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/071/071_003.gif)

3. Ani oAAbudoo All<u>a</u>ha wa**i**ttaqoohu waa<u>t</u>eeAAoon**i**

3\. "That ye should worship  
God, fear Him,  
And obey me:

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/071/071_004.gif)

4. Yaghfir lakum min <u>th</u>unoobikum wayu-akhkhirkum il<u>a</u>
ajalin musamman inna ajala All<u>a</u>hi i<u>tha</u> j<u>a</u>a
l<u>a</u> yu-akhkharu law kuntum taAAlamoon**a**

4\. "So He may forgive you  
Your sins and give you  
Respite for a stated Term:  
For when the Term given  
By God is accomplished,  
It cannot be put forward:  
If ye only knew."

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/071/071_005.gif)

5. Q<u>a</u>la rabbi innee daAAawtu qawmee laylan
wanah<u>a</u>r<u>a</u>**n**

5\. He, said: "O my Lord!  
I have called to my People  
Night and day:

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/071/071_006.gif)

6. Falam yazidhum duAA<u>a</u>-ee ill<u>a</u> fir<u>a</u>r<u>a</u>**n**

6\. "But my call only  
Increases (their) flight  
(From the Right).

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/071/071_007.gif)

7. Wa-innee kullam<u>a</u> daAAawtuhum litaghfira lahum jaAAaloo
a<u>sa</u>biAAahum fee <u>atha</u>nihim wa**i**staghshaw
thiy<u>a</u>bahum waa<u>s</u>arroo wa**i**stakbaroo
istikb<u>a</u>r<u>a</u>**n**

7\. "And every time I have  
Called to them, that Thou  
Mightest forgive them,  
They have (only) thrust  
Their fingers into their ears,  
Covered themselves up with  
Their garments, grown obstinate,  
And given themselves up  
To arrogance.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/071/071_008.gif)

8. Thumma innee daAAawtuhum jih<u>a</u>r<u>a</u>**n**

8\. "So I have called to them  
Aloud;

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/071/071_009.gif)

9. Thumma innee aAAlantu lahum waasrartu lahum isr<u>a</u>r<u>a</u>**n**

9\. "Further I have spoken  
To them in public  
And secretly in private,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/071/071_010.gif)

10. Faqultu istaghfiroo rabbakum innahu k<u>a</u>na
ghaff<u>a</u>r<u>a</u>**n**

10\. "Saying, "Ask forgiveness  
From your Lord;  
For He is Oft-Forgiving;

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/071/071_011.gif)

11. Yursili a**l**ssam<u>a</u>a AAalaykum midr<u>a</u>r<u>a</u>**n**

11\. "He will send rain  
To you in abundance;

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/071/071_012.gif)

12. Wayumdidkum bi-amw<u>a</u>lin wabaneena wayajAAal lakum
jann<u>a</u>tin wayajAAal lakum anh<u>a</u>r<u>a</u>**n**

12\. Give you increase  
In wealth and sons;  
And bestow on you  
Gardens and bestow on you  
Rivers (of flowing water).

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/071/071_013.gif)

13. M<u>a</u> lakum l<u>a</u> tarjoona lill<u>a</u>hi
waq<u>a</u>r<u>a</u>**n**

13\. "What is the matter  
With you, that ye  
Place not your hope  
For kindness and long-suffering  
In God,—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/071/071_014.gif)

14. Waqad khalaqakum a<u>t</u>w<u>a</u>r<u>a</u>**n**

14\. "Seeing that it is He  
That has created you  
In diverse stages?

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/071/071_015.gif)

15. Alam taraw kayfa khalaqa All<u>a</u>hu sabAAa
sam<u>a</u>w<u>a</u>tin <u>t</u>ib<u>a</u>q<u>a</u>**n**

15\. "See ye not  
How God has created  
The seven heavens  
One above another,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/071/071_016.gif)

16. WajaAAala alqamara feehinna nooran wajaAAala a**l**shshamsa
sir<u>a</u>j<u>a</u>**n**

16\. "And made the moon  
A light in their midst,  
And made the sun  
As a (Glorious) Lamp?

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/071/071_017.gif)

17. Wa**A**ll<u>a</u>hu anbatakum mina al-ar<u>d</u>i
nab<u>a</u>t<u>a</u>**n**

17\. "And God has produced  
You from the earth,  
Growing (gradually),

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/071/071_018.gif)

18. Thumma yuAAeedukum feeh<u>a</u> wayukhrijukum
ikhr<u>a</u>j<u>a</u>**n**

18\. "And in the End  
He will return you  
Into the (earth),  
And raise you forth  
(Again at the Resurrection)?

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/071/071_019.gif)

19. Wa**A**ll<u>a</u>hu jaAAala lakumu al-ar<u>d</u>a bis<u>ata</u>**n**

19\. "And God has made  
The earth for you  
As a carpet (spread out),

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/071/071_020.gif)

20. Litaslukoo minh<u>a</u> subulan fij<u>a</u>j<u>a</u>**n**

20\. "That ye may go about  
Therein, in spacious roads."

